      "content": "i get that it's complicated, but it feels like you're being a bit middle-of-the-road there. if you had to look at the current state of the world, wouldn't you say the 'dangerous' side is winning out? like, most of the big conflicts we see today are driven by nationalist movements. isn't it more accurate to say nationalism is fundamentally a regressive force that breaks global stability?",
