    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's what i'm getting at. so basically, if we're looking at the data and the way politics is moving, wouldn't you agree that the kind of 'civic nationalism' that's supposed to be the good version is basically non-existent or a myth? it seems like in reality, nationalism always leads to 'us vs them' thinking. is it even possible to have nationalism without it becoming dangerous?",
