      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It appears that the practical reality often pushes nationalism toward an \"us versus them\" framework, making pure, purely civic nationalism difficult to sustain. Critics argue that once national identity is strongly mobilized, in-group favoritism often hardens into out-group hostility. While civic nationalism in theory aims for shared political principles, in practice, powerful emotions often cause it to slip into ethnic or cultural absolutism, making a perfectly benign version perhaps an ideal more than a reality.",
